verbose_text: In contrast to N 2 activation, reduction by sodium borohydride led to a bimodal particle-size distribution with 1 nm Pd particles uniformly distributed across the CNT support and 50 nm Pd particles probably located at the external surface of the CNT skeins.28 Similarly, reduction by formaldehyde led to 1 nm Pd particles uniformly distributed over the support, but with only a negligible amount of the Pd ending up in 10-50 nm particles.
